---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy" description="What Storyteller Toolbox stores, where it lives, and what never happens to it.">
  <article class="policy">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="effective">Effective 2026-07-11 · applies to storytellertoolbox.com</p>

    <div class="tldr card">
      <h2>The short version</h2>
      <p>
        Everything you create here is <strong>yours</strong>. It lives in your browser and —
        only if you choose — in <strong>your own Google Drive</strong>, purely so you can
        continue where you left off on another device. This site has <strong>no server, no
        accounts, no analytics, and no ads</strong>. We never receive your content, and we
        never evaluate, sell, share, or monetize it. We couldn't if we wanted to — it never
        passes through anything we operate.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>What this site stores, and where</h2>
    <p>
      Storyteller Toolbox is a static website. When you use it, it stores data in exactly
      two places, both controlled by you:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Your browser (localStorage).</strong> The documents you create — prep
        sheets, notes, journal entries today, and future document types such as maps, stat
        blocks, and initiative trackers as the tool grows — plus small preferences like your
        light/dark theme choice. This data stays on your device. Clearing your browser's
        site data deletes it.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Your Google Drive (optional).</strong> If you click
        <em>☁ Save to Drive</em> on the Sheet Builder, your documents are written to a
        single file named <code>storyteller-toolbox-data.json</code> in your own Google
        Drive. That's the entire purpose of the integration: keeping your progress —
        whatever you write or generate, from prep notes to prayers to whole campaign
        journals — available for cross-device continuation.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="google-drive">The Google Drive connection, precisely</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>What is sent:</strong> only the contents of the documents you created on
        this site — the same text you see on your sheets. Nothing else: no browsing
        activity, no usage statistics, no device information beyond what Google's own
        sign-in requires.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>When:</strong> only when you click <em>Save to Drive</em> or
        <em>Load</em>. There is no background syncing.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Where it goes:</strong> directly from your browser to Google Drive over
        HTTPS. It does not pass through any server of ours — there isn't one.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>What the site can access:</strong> the connection uses Google's
        <code>drive.file</code> permission, the narrowest available — the site can only
        see and modify the one backup file it created. It cannot read, list, or touch
        anything else in your Drive.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Taking it back:</strong> click <em>Disconnect</em> on the Sheet Builder to
        revoke access, or manage it any time at
        <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions">myaccount.google.com/permissions</a>.
        To erase the backup itself, delete <code>storyteller-toolbox-data.json</code> from
        your Drive. Done — no residue anywhere, because no copy ever existed anywhere else.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Storyteller Toolbox's use of information received from Google APIs adheres to the
      <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy">Google
      API Services User Data Policy</a>, including the Limited Use requirements.
    </p>

    <h2>What we never do</h2>
    <p>
      We never evaluate, analyze, profile, sell, rent, share, or train anything on your
      data. We serve no ads and run no analytics or tracking of any kind. The architecture
      makes these promises structural rather than aspirational: your content moves only
      between your browser and your Google Drive.
    </p>

    <h2>Third parties</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Google</strong> handles sign-in and Drive storage under
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy">Google's privacy policy</a> when you
        choose to connect.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>GitHub Pages</strong> hosts the site's static files; like any web host,
        GitHub may log standard request data (such as IP addresses) per the
        <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement">GitHub
        privacy statement</a>. We have no access to, and make no use of, such logs.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Changes &amp; contact</h2>
    <p>
      If this policy ever changes, the new version appears on this page with a new
      effective date — and the promises above are the point of the project, so don't
      expect them to move. Questions or concerns:
      <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/seriousd6/">get in touch</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .policy {
    max-width: 46rem;
  }

  .policy h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    color: var(--color-statblock);
  }

  .effective {
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
  }

  .tldr {
    margin-block: var(--space-6);
  }

  .policy ul {
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    margin-block: var(--space-4);
  }
</style>
